# shadcn/ui (desktop renderer)

Use shadcn/ui components, layouts, and theme tokens. Do not build custom UI primitives unless required for domain-specific UI (React Flow nodes, canvas).

## Do

- Import from `@/components/ui/*` (Button, Select, Textarea, Alert, Card, ScrollArea, etc.)
- Use semantic tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-sidebar`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`
- Add new components via CLI: `npx shadcn@latest add <name> -y` in `apps/desktop`
- Use `@tabler/icons-react` for icons
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes

## Don't

- Raw `<button>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>` with hand-rolled Tailwind when shadcn exists
- Hardcoded palette classes (`gray-500`, `blue-600`, `red-50`) for app chrome
- Copy/paste shadcn source from the web — always use the CLI
- Mix icon libraries

## Example

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button.js";
<Button variant="outline" size="sm">Open</Button>

// ❌ BAD
<button className="rounded border border-gray-300 px-3 py-1">Open</button>
```

Read skill `shadcn-ui` for preset, paths, and CLI commands.
